#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:601
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mount management commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:603
#, no-wrap
msgid "`mount` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:606
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `mount` command allows you to mount and view the logical drives in the tree.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:607
#, no-wrap
msgid "mount [-option] [device] [directory]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:613
#, no-wrap
msgid "[root]# mount /dev/sda7 /home\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:625
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                                                                    |\n"
"|--------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-n`   | Mount without writing to `/etc/mtab`.                                          |\n"
"| `-t`   | To indicate the type of file system to use.                                    |\n"
"| `-a`   | Mounts all filesystems mentioned in `/etc/fstab`.                              |\n"
"| `-r`   | Mounts the file system read-only (equivalent to `-o ro`).                      |\n"
"| `-w`   | Mounts the file system read/write, by default (equivalent `-o rw`).            |\n"
"| `-o`   | Argument followed by a comma-separated list of options (`remount`, `ro`, ...). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:629
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The `mount` command alone displays all mounted file systems.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:630
#, no-wrap
msgid "`umount` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:633
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `umount` command is used to unmount logical drives.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:634
#, no-wrap
msgid "umount [-option] [device] [directory]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:640
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[root]# umount /home\n"
"[root]# umount /dev/sda7\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:651
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                                        |\n"
"|--------|----------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-n`   | Unmount without writing to `/etc/mtab`.            |\n"
"| `-r`   | If unmount fails, remount as read-only.            |\n"
"| `-f`   | Force unmount.                                     |\n"
"| `-a`   | Unmount all filesystems mentioned in `/etc/fstab`. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:655
#, no-wrap
msgid "    When disassembling, you must not stay below the mounting point. Otherwise, the following error message is displayed: `device is busy`.\n"
msgstr ""

