#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:830
#, no-wrap
msgid "Basic permissions of files and directories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:833
#, no-wrap
msgid "The description of **file permissions** is as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:840
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| File permissions | Description                                                                        |\n"
"| :---------------:| -------------                                                                      |\n"
"| r                | Read. Allows reading a file (`cat`, `less`, ...) and copying a file (`cp`, ...).   |\n"
"| w                | Write. Allows modification of the file content (`cat`, `>>`, `vim`, ...).          |\n"
"| x                | Execute. Considers the file as an e**X**ecutable (binary or script).               |\n"
"| -                | No right                                                                           |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:842
#, no-wrap
msgid "The description of **directory permissions** is as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:849
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Directory permissions | Description                                                                        |\n"
"| :---------------:     | -------------                                                                      |\n"
"| r                     | Read. Allows reading the contents of a directory (`ls -R`).                        |\n"
"| w                     | Write. Allows you to create, and delete files/directories in this directory, such as commands `mkdir`, `rmdir`, `rm`, `touch`, and so on.  |\n"
"| x                     | Execute. Allows descending in the directory (`cd`).                                |\n"
"| -                     | No right                                                                           |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:853
#, no-wrap
msgid "    For the permissions of a directory, `r` and `x` usually appear at the same time. Moving or renaming a file depends on whether the directory where the file is located has `w` permission, and so does deleting a file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:854
#, no-wrap
msgid "User type corresponding to basic permission"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:861
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| User type| Description                    |\n"
"| :---:   | ------                         |\n"
"| u        | Owner                          |\n"
"| g        | Owner group                    |\n"
"| o        | Others users                   |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:865
#, no-wrap
msgid "    In some commands it is possible to designate everyone with **a** (_all_). **a = ugo**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:866
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attribute management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:869
#, no-wrap
msgid "The display of rights is done with the command `ls -l`. It is the last 9 characters of the block of 10. More precisely 3 times 3 characters.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:870
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[root]# ls -l /tmp/myfile\n"
"-rwxrw-r-x  1  root  sys  ... /tmp/myfile\n"
"  1  2  3       4     5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:883
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Part |\tDescription                                                   |\n"
"|-----|---------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| 1   | Owner (**u**ser) permissions, here `rwx`                      |\n"
"| 2   | Owner group permissions (**g**roup), here `rw-`               |\n"
"| 3   | Other users' permissions (**o**thers), here `r-x`             |\n"
"| 4   | File owner                                                    |\n"
"| 5   | Group owner of the file                                       |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:885
#, no-wrap
msgid "By default, the _owner_ of a file is the one who creates it. The _group_ of the file is the group of the owner who created the file. The _others_ are those which are not concerned by the previous cases.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:887
#, no-wrap
msgid "The attributes are changed with the `chmod` command.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:889
#, no-wrap
msgid "Only the administrator and the owner of a file can change the rights of a file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:890
#, no-wrap
msgid "`chmod` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:893
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `chmod` command allows you to change the access permissions to a file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:894
#, no-wrap
msgid "chmod [option] mode file\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:901
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option |\tObservation                                                           |\n"
"|--------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-R`   |  Recursively change the permissions of the directory and all files under the directory. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:905
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The rights of files and directories are not dissociated. For some operations, it will be necessary to know the rights of the directory containing the file. A write-protected file can be deleted by another user as long as the rights of the directory containing it allow this user to perform this operation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
